  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf \u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0b95\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b85\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bc1\u0b9a\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bcd\u0baf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bb5\u0bc7\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The new president should be elected by consensus",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "The National Peace Council of Sri Lanka has emphasized that it is the duty of the leaders of the political parties in Parliament to elect a new president based on consensus until the time comes when they can hold national elections and receive a new mandate from the people.",
        "The details of the report issued by the Peace Council, which has Finance Minister Jagan Perera as its Executive Director on Saturday 16th, are as follows;",
        "Following the confirmation of President Gotabaya Rajapaksa's resignation, all eyes are now on the presidential election to be held in Parliament. This is not a normal practice. One is the result of a popular uprising of sorts.",
        "Above all it is the power of the people vested in the Government by the Constitution (Article 4).",
        "The National Peace Council is deeply concerned about the campaigns and speeches being carried out to garner support for the presidential election while ignoring the ground realities of a people's revolt against individuals and systems that have ruined the country economically, socially and morally.",
        "It is noteworthy that the members of parliament participate in this election to elect a new president with a mandate that has actually been weakened by the popular uprising. This is especially true for members of the ruling party and the former government who have lost the moral justification to rule the country.",
        "In such a situation, we believe it is the duty of the leaders of the political parties in Parliament to decide to elect a new president based on consensus until the time comes to hold national elections and receive a new mandate directly from the people.",
        "We believe that the new president should be able to work with all parties, experts in the country, local and international organizations and above all, he should be acceptable to the people of the country.",
        "Governance is not merely the exercise of power, but the protection of the rights of each and the well-being of all.",
        "There is a need for the President to win the trust of all citizens, especially the young men and women who have to face a polluted future.",
        "The immediate duties of the new President are to bring in the 21st Amendment to the Constitution and set dates for the parliamentary elections and provincial councils elections as soon as possible."
      ],
